I took my mom out to lunch here as we were both craving BBQ.  Neither of us have been here so we were anxious to see how’ve they were.  She got the pork sandwich with onion rings and I got the brisket plate with fries and onion rings.  As with any bbq restaurant, I like my brisket to be end cuts with some fat.  That’s where all the taste is.  They honored my request and it didn’t disappoint.  The bark had a real good taste and the fat melted in the mouth.  Fries were fresh cut and the onion rings were beer battered.  Pork sandwich was a large sandwich by any standard.  We were both pleased and will be back.

We ordered pick up (first time eating here). My order was brought to the car and it was so delicious. I love that the sauce wasn’t extremely sweet and had a slight kick to it. The sandwich was loaded with meat and the brisket is very tender. We cannot wait to come back!

My favorites are any of the meats, the Brunswick stew, hash brown casserole, BBQ beans and okra. Everything is to die for! Wish I had ordered dessert!!

Best ribs I have had to date. So  much meat on them for such a great price! Brisket was a little dry, but the fried okra was delicious. Can't wait to try the rest of the menu!

If it were possible to give this place negative stars I would but unfortunately that isn’t an option. Since I absolutely HAD to share this horrible experience I guess this is sufficient. We had to pay before we received any food which was odd but we decided to give it a try. It felt like almost immediately after sitting down our “waitress” (because she barley talked to us) brought out our food and at first glance the food looked pretty decent, I ordered a half rack of ribs, fries and coleslaw and my girlfriend ordered a turkey sandwich with fries and greens. From this moment on  everything went downhill. My girlfriends turkey sandwich was EXTREMELY dry. The turkey had no flavor at all and there was no toppings like cheese or anything except two straggly pickles. But even the pickles couldn’t give any moisture to it. On the other hand the greens were practically drowning in the juice which consisted more juice than actual greens. Interestingly enough her food wasn’t even the worst thing on the table. My $18 ribs were beyond disgusting, they were SO dry and had absolutely Zero flavor. I remember before we started eating we said a quick prayer over the food and I think that may be the only reason we survived the visit. After forcing myself to eat two of the $18 ribs I took one bite into the third and I couldn’t take anymore. After barely enduring the atrocious ribs I tasted the coleslaw and not to my surprise, IT WAS DRY!! I have never in my life heard of dry coleslaw but somehow they pulled it off, and on top of that the coleslaw didn’t even a decent flavor. The only thing on that plate that I could eat was the fries and even those weren’t very good. By the time I stopped eating I looked at my girlfriend and said I have to ask for a refund because it was completely insane that I paid $30 (in total) for the food and it was that bad. After receiving my refund for the ribs( since they only wanted to give me my money back for one meal because my girlfriend ate the fries) we started getting up to leave and as we were walking out the door I said “have a nice day!” And not one said anything and we awkwardly walked out. Absolutely horrible customer service I wouldn’t recommend 🤮

1st time visit. The employees were wonderful. However, the ribs tasted boiled. They did not have a smoke line. The banana pudding tasted like instant pudding. Sadly, the overall food was not up to my expectations of BBQ.

I asked for scrambled eggs with cheese and mushrooms and I received plain scrambled eggs. I ordered a side of bacon thinking I would get 2 but instead I got 1. I had to take my business to Jr’s loghouse to get some good breakfast.

Disclaimer: I have been eating at Spiced Right for over 2 years and have never had a bad experience until now. Ordered pickup - full rack, corn souffle, hashbrown casserole, and Cole slaw. When we arrived, they were out of corn souffle. We were asked if we wanted another side but we did not because we figured the 2 other sides would suffice ( prior experiences my husband and I have always shared 2 sides and have had plenty between the two of us). When we got home, we saw the sides were small; one side was barely enough for one person. I then had to cook more sides on what was supposed to be an evening of not worrying about cooking. Thought the ribs would make up for that experience but they were the worst ribs I have ever had, maybe even worse than Dreamland up the road. The meat was so tough you could barely get it off the bone. Maybe it's a bad thing I have eaten here before and the ribs have always fell off the bone, but tonight, they were awful. Ended up having to make my family sandwiches after everything because we were still hungry after spending 40$ on our meal. In the past, I have always enjoyed Spiced Right. I even had them cater my son's 1st birthday and made sure to tell the guests about this "hidden gem" in Roswell. This experience, however, left a sour taste in my mouth. I do not think I would come back unless this experience was reconciled.

In a effort to give business to small businesses I placed my order...Combo Plate with Pork and Brisket, brunswick stew and corn souffle, BBQ Melt with pork, hash brown casserole and banana pudding.  Every single item was Perfection!!!!!!!!!!!!  All of meats were cooked perfectly and so tender!! The sauce was delicious. The sides were so flavorful and the pudding was fabulous!!!!!  Spiced Right you have gained a customer for life.  Well done!!!  Thanks for knowing how to perfectly cook BBQ!!!!

EDITED: Read to the end. Passed by this place thousands of times, decided to try it.  Should have passed by again!  Not sure how you burn onion rings!  Brisket was bland and dry.  Ribs uninspiring!  Their saying "If the Colonel had our recipe, he'd be a General"  should be amended to "he'd be dishonorably discharged." Called the restaurant & spoke with Rob, the manager.  He apologized profusely for how bad everything was.  Offered either another meal or my money back.  Took the meal because of other positive reviews.  Onion rings were better; not flavored to my liking, but that's a personal taste.  Brisket moist. Ribs were meaty.  Overall, a much better meal.  Unfortunately, it took my complaining for them to have better quality control.  I would recommend you try this place for yourselves. Flavor of everything not exactly to my liking, but then neither is the "bloomin' onion."
The Chipotle Brisket Tacos are excellent! The banana pudding is also very good! We cater from this place quite a bit and never disappoints!

Absolutely love this little old place; feels like it hasn't changed in 20 years(in a good way). I told him that we drove here from Seattle and was looking at Atlanta cuz we may move here and he briefly told me about the area and his experience living here while I was waiting for my order. 5 words. Hair, lemon seed, unseasoned food. And I got it all for the high price of $16. First off as a BBQ restaurant, I expect the meat to BE SEASONED. So I ordered the BBQ sandwich plate which comes with two sides (I got the baked beans and fries) and a banana pudding. Everything came up to $16 and change. I expected some good tasting food for this price. EVERYTHING was under seasoned if not seasoned at all. The meat in the sandwich tasted like cardboard because again, they didn't season it. Also the baked beans I got as a side has pulled pork in it that is also not seasoned. THEN I open up my banana pudding and the first thing I see is a hair...I scoop the hair out and take a couple of bites and I then find a lemon seed (hoping that's what it was at least). I don't know if they make the pudding with lemon or what but that's what I got. A lemon seed. So all in all for $16 I got a hair, lemon seed and unseasoned food. Enjoy
Love eating here!!

We (my husband and our 2 kids) went there on Saturday night after having several locals tell us this was the best BBQ in the area.  THEY WERE RIGHT!!!!  I can cook my own smoked ribs but these were very tasty.  I got collards because I didn't want the fries ("starch" but fries are my weakness) but my son got the fries.....THEY WERE SO GOOD.  The collards were as well.  My husband got brisket and pulled pork and my other soon got a BBQ Sandwich.....not to mention the pinion rings has a batter that is delicious. The bartender (young lady) was friendly and the young man clearing the tables and serving was very quite but I did get him to crack a smile....they even had live music and the man singing was really good.....It is appears to be a come as you are bar but there were couples in there that looked as if they could have been city officials.  We are only here for 7 days for the Perfect Game Baseball games and we planned on going back for breakfast and dinner as soon as we get a break in our sschedule.

Great food. Not great attitudes. The best person there is Nicole! But now we are complaining when a lot of people order online for TAKEOUT and how it backs up their system.... I thought they like a lot of business... hence why they are in business... but then complain that no one left a tip on individual orders for takeout... If you are going to complain you will lose a lot of business. If we were all dining in then yes a tip should be given. But take out? Little extreme if you ask me by getting upset about no tips when there was about $160 spent from individual orders. You are charging prices based on cost and labor. If that is not enough then raise your prices and stop complaining to paying customers, because that is how you lose them. *side note instead of complaining about our tips how about we make sure that our orders are right and we are not missing items that we paid for like Orange Juice.

It's a challenge to navigate the awkward parking lot but the smell is worth it. Sitting outside next to the traffic zooming by on Alpharetta St is available but I chose inside. My ribs and and my husband brisket was so tender, that I could cut through with my fork. The greens were seasoned just right and I am picky about my greens. Potatoe salad was just like granny's. We really wanted to try the corn souffle, so we got a side of that and the banana pudding. The souffle was really good, but sweet and that banana pudding had to be scratch made. No instant pudding there. My husband and I kind of bickered over it. He got the most🙁. We went on a Saturday and the live music added to the atmosphere. Don't go here expecting it to be fancy, it's a hole in the wall in a really nice area, but the food makes up for it. Customer service was great too. Will definitely be going back. Also they support our troops past and present with a 20% discount.  If it's your first time here and you're on a date or with a friend, get the two meat and two sides combo. It's more than enough food two ppl.
